Terence Strange was an English cricketer. He was a right-handed batsman and right-arm fast bowler who played for Oxfordshire.
Having made his Minor Counties Championship debut for the team during the 1953 season, Strange made a single List A appearance, in 1970, his final season with the team. From the tailend, he scored 2 not out with the bat, and took figures of 0-21 from 9 overs with the ball.
